In addition, a high rate of lactate dehydrogenase (LDH), aminotransferase aspartate (AST), alanine aminotransferase (ALT) and creatine kinase (CK) may also be involved in establishing the prognosis.
These enzymes are widely expressed within several organs, especially at the heart and liver level, and are released in case of tissue lesions.
