Three vaccination strategies are researched.
First, researchers are trying to create a full virus vaccine.
The use of such a virus, whether inactive or dead, is intended to cause a rapid immune response of the human body in the event of a new infection in the COVID-19.
A second strategy, subunit-based vaccines, aims to create a vaccine that sensitizes the immune system to certain subunits of the virus.
In the case of SARS-CoV-2, these research focuses on the specular protein S that helps the virus to infiltrate into the receptor of the enzyme ACE 2.
A third strategy is the nuclear-acid-based vaccines (DNA or DNA vaccination, a new vaccine creation technique).
